updates.update_content:
Brief update ...
I've confirmed commissioning of the cover art from Kasha Mika;
Most recent playtest series produced some great insights into 'seek relief from the horror' and how a small tweak can encourage more players to build their individual and collective history together;
... also that player's first instinct is to throw their Anchor, the last person they care about and who might care about them, into the COnspiracy's crosshairs in return for reducing Stress (while giving the GM a valued NPC for climactic scenes)!

campaign.risks:
Risks and challenges
This is our second Kickstarter, 'Pax Cthuliana' being our first and delivered on time. 'Svalbard' is currently in a developing stage. We need the opening to change some of its contents due to rewards, plus it takes some time to prepare the scenario for different versions. The fulfillment is via DriveThruRPG. This ensures a secure and predictable dispatch of both digital and POD versions of the scenario. Being Norwegians, we also need to pay for a professional proofreading;
Learn about accountability on Kickstarter

updates.update_content:
Thanks to everyone who has pledged so far. Just one full day in and we're already a full finger towards our funding goal. Lookin' good! Let's hope we can keep pace to hit our mark and more.
Happy that we're all excited to jump back into cyberpunk worlds. Tell your friends and gaming associates :)
//K_B
